    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen trying to build Neovim to WebAssembly using Emscripten on WSL, cmake.deps fails during the libuv build with:\n\n```\n/home/rawan/NeovimWeb/external/neovim/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/linux.c:44:10: fatal error: 'sys/epoll.h' file not found\n   44 | #include <sys/epoll.h>\n      |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\n```\nI have disabled epoll and eventfd features by passing this in .deps configuration:\n```\n-DWITH_LIBUV__WITH_LINUX_EPOLL=OFF \\\n-DWITH_LIBUV__WITH_LINUX_EVENTFD=OFF \\\n-DWITH_LIBUV__WITH_LINUX_INOTIFY=OFF \\\n-DWITH_LIBUV__WITH_LINUX_SIGNALED=OFF \\\n-DWITH_LIBUV__WITH_POLL=ON \\\n-DWITH_LIBUV__WITH_KQUEUE=ON\n```\nbut the build still tries to include sys/epoll.h and fails.\n\nEnvironment:\nOS: Ubuntu 22.04 (WSL2)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ncmake.deps should propagate the Emscripten toolchain to libuv. So, I think this should make libuv detect that it is being built for WASM, skip sys/epoll.h, and use backends like poll/kqueue instead.",
